From 4c471723e3ed3addf57852ea05de7f38165ce911 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Saverio Pavone <pavone.lawyer@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 16:17:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] v4l2-video: add HEVC Main 8-bit 4:2:0 decode
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Mirror the H.264 path for HEVC on rkvdec's V4L2 stateless API: advertise
VK_KHR_video_decode_h265, translate the Vulkan std structures into the V4L2
HEVC controls (SPS, PPS, scaling matrix, short/long-term RPS, decode params),
and parse the slice segment header for the fields the hardware needs. The RPS
goes through the EXT_SPS ST/LT controls that VDPU381 requires. The bit-reader
and start-code helpers are factored out of the H.264 parser into a shared
v4l2vk_bitreader.h.

Scope is Main profile, 8-bit, 4:2:0; weighted prediction is not parsed
(the long-term-reference DPB flag is also not wired yet — no test stream had
long-term references). Validated byte-exact against ffmpeg on an RK3588 across
I/P/B, more than one short-term RPS, and 360p/720p/1080p including cropped
sizes, and playing in WebKitGTK through a small GStreamer bridge.

Signed-off-by: Saverio Pavone <pavone.lawyer@gmail.com>
Assisted-by: Claude:claude-opus-4-8
